Greater prior uncertainty (before interaction) over a partner’s relative preferences was associated with increased HI (ρ[

βparref

] = 0.25, p=0.01, p[fdr]=0.04) but not SI, according with prior work (Barnby et al., 2022). There was no uncorrected association between prior uncertainty over absolute preferences with either attribution. This suggests that expectations of greater difference, irrespective of one’s true difference between self-other, may exaggerate beliefs about the intentional harm of others.

